00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:24,840
How long have you worked as a model?

259
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:27,009
I think I worked as a model...

260
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:29,179
- only for 5 to 6 years. - Right.

261
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:31,449
A while ago, we did a photo shoot...

262
00:08:31,450 --> 00:08:33,780
- to promote the drama. - I bet she did a great job.

263
00:08:34,420 --> 00:08:35,749
- She was so professional. - Of course.

264
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,720
I was so impressed the whole time.

265
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:39,560
He kept talking to me...

266
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:41,166
- during the photo shoot. - He was envious.

267
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:42,190
She was so cool.

268
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,730
You have to stay focused.

269
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,729
No wonder.

270
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:47,429
- She definitely had the model vibe. - She was really cool.

271
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:49,229
(The photos from their intense concentration)

272
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:50,899
- We should get going now. - Shall we?

273
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,276
(It's time for their first spare time.)

274
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,839
- My gosh. It's gotten long. - Yes, it's so long.

275
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,076
- There are so many cards now. - What is that?

276
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:57,409
Here are our first Whenever Guests.

277
00:08:57,410 --> 00:08:59,980
"Won Hyun Sik and Seo Chung Rok."

278
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:02,649
"We can fly in the sky and turn into animals."

279
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:04,626
"Sometimes, we can even become the lead characters of movies."

280
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:07,780
"With a click, imagination turns into reality."

281
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:10,619
"We spend 16 hours together every day."

282
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:14,090
"We're soulmates with the same sense of humor too."

283
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:17,559
"We'd love to hang out with you at the mecca of zoomers."

284
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,860
The mecca of zoomers?

285
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,959
- Fly in the sky? - It said, "click,".

286
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,499
- Photos? - so they must be photographers.

287
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,769
They can become lead characters of movies.

288
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:25,099
Could it be...

289
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,540
- Fly in the sky? - the photo booth?

290
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:29,009
- Like instant photo booths? - They set up different themes...

291
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:31,540
- for each booth. - Really?

292
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,679
Each booth has a different theme.

293
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:34,409
- We must be there by 11am. - Let's go.

294
00:09:34,410 --> 00:09:35,709
- We have a lot of time left. - We can get going.

295
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:37,049
- We can walk there. - Sure.

296
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:38,286
- Sounds good. - Shall we get going?

297
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:39,379
My gosh.

298
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:41,419
Is there something wrong with your eyes? You have sunglasses on.

299
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:42,490
My eyes hurt.

300
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:44,019
- Really? - My eyes hurt.

301
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:45,619
Sunglasses are great for UV protection.

302
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:46,660
They're great.

303
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,229
(Heading to their first spare time)

304
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:50,670
It's within walking distance, right?

305
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:55,930
- We can be there in 18 minutes. - Then we'll be there soon.

306
00:09:56,070 --> 00:09:58,130
- The weather is warming up. - Right.

307
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:00,070
- It's the perfect day for a walk. - Yes.

308
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,869
What did you do for the Lunar New Year?

309
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:05,139
I went to my parents' house, and spent it with my family.

310
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,209
- Really? - Yes.

311
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:07,839
Did you stay there long? Or was it a short visit?

312
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,549
I went the day before New Year's Day, and stayed for two days.

313
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:11,650
- You spent a lot of them there. - Yes.

314
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,050
That's not easy these days.

315
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,620
Right.

316
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:18,350
(The end of conversation)

317
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:19,819
What about you, Som?

318
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,320
I didn't go anywhere.

319
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:24,090
I climbed Mount Gwanak with my mom and older sister.

320
00:10:24,930 --> 00:10:25,959
We went to Yeonjuam.

321
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,299
- Mount Gwanak? - Yeonjuam?

322
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,000
Yes. I heard that Mount Gwanak had good energy.

323
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,400
(Chuckling)

324
00:10:31,401 --> 00:10:32,561
Did you get some good energy?

325
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:35,499
- Did you get some good energy? - Yes, I got a lot of good energy.

326
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,910
- Use up the energy today. - Let's use up that energy.

327
00:10:38,310 --> 00:10:39,679
Som is funny.

328
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,109
She went all the way to Yeonjuam for good energy.

329
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:42,110
(Looking forward to the energy from Yeonjuam)

330
00:10:42,111 --> 00:10:45,009
By the way, I see a lot of good restaurants here...

331
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:46,549
in Junggok-dong and Gunja-dong.

332
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:49,396
- It has a lot of good restaurants. - I already spotted so many of them.

333
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:50,989
I remember having meals...

334
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:54,160
around here with my family when I used to live in Junggok-dong.

335
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:56,860
My gosh. There's a ton of good restaurants here.

336
00:10:57,530 --> 00:10:59,300
- Let's go straight. Yes. - Go straight?

337
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,460
- Let's cross. - Should we? Fifteen seconds.

338
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,000
That's enough time.

339
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:05,060
I remember this street from my college days.

340
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,340
This was the bus street.

341
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:09,016
- Junggok-dong and Myeonmok-dong. - It's a special for Yeon Shik.

342
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,040
(Getting nostalgic)

343
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:11,839
We came to Gunja-dong for Yeon Shik.

344
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:15,239
(The street brings back memories for the Sejong University graduate.)

345
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,786
Konkuk University students would come here.

346
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:18,079
- Sejong University students too. - Sejong University students too.

347
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,880
- Also, Hanyang University students. - Right.

348
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,489
And we'd hang out around Hanyang University too.

349
00:11:22,490 --> 00:11:23,519
- You would? - Around Wangsimni?

350
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:24,690
Yes. We'd go to Wangsimni.

351
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:28,360
There are several repair shops around here too.

352
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,659
(The staff members are chattering.)

353
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:31,730
What?

354
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:35,099
- Where are you leading us? - No. I set it...

355
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,200
No. This is the right address, isn't it?

356
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,940
Old memories distracted you, so you weren't even checking.

357
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:42,539
(Checking the name card again)

358
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:44,900
- They're not the ones... - Did you type in the second one?

359
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:47,880
- My gosh. - Unbelievable. Seriously.

360
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:50,109
- We're visiting two places today. - My gosh.

361
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:51,209
- You were supposed... - He...

362
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:52,970
- was like... - to lead us to the soulmates.

363
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,950
You little...

364
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,890
We came pretty far.

365
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:02,690
Where are you taking us?

366
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,700
- I got distracted by my memories. - I mean...

367
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,299
- Myeonmok-dong... - You know what?

368
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,530
- Let's go to Sejong University. - He got so excited.

369
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:13,376
- Maybe it was the cafe earlier. - We can be there in seven minutes.

370
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,599
- Let's hurry. Where is it? - We can just go up a bit from here.

371
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,740
- Come on. - Gosh.

372
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:19,110
- Do you know what's great, though? - What is it?

373
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:21,510
By the time we get there, we'll be right on time.

374
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:24,579
- Come on. Which way? Here? - We'll have five minutes to spare.

375
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:26,060
- We have to go this way. - This way?

376
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:29,420
Wait. Then we're heading into my old neighborhood.

377
00:12:30,290 --> 00:12:32,970
It's not important whether or not we go into your old neighborhood.

378
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:34,659
I'm taking a trip down memory lane.

379
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:36,780
(He snaps out of it and goes back to being Navi Yoo.)

380
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:40,629
I feel so reassured having three of my co-stars.

381
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:41,830
- You do? - Yes.

382
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:43,770
Just focus on guiding us.

383
00:12:44,970 --> 00:12:46,600
- We feel reassured too. - Okay?

384
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:48,770
- You're happy to have me, right? - Yes.

385
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:51,670
Who knew you'd give us a tour by taking the long way around?

386
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:54,940
Yes. This is the spot.

387
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:57,610
We'll arrive at Junggok Station if we go straight.

388
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,020
- Gosh. - I used to go straight,

389
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:03,290
and take the subway at Junggok Station.

390
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:05,589
- When you were in school? - When I was in school.

391
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:08,066
Well, I took the bus to school and the subway when I went out.

392
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:10,530
How many times are you going to talk about your college days?

393
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:13,060
This is a long street.

394
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,859
- I'm just feeling nostalgic. - Who cares about the bus?

395
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:16,529
- Let me just talk... - Don't talk about your old days.

396
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:19,070
- Find the place. - We can just go straight.

397
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,469
- It's at the end of the street. - Come on.

398
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:23,870
- He's bragging about his school. - Seriously. Why...

399
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:26,970
He started with the bus stop. How many times will he mention it?

400
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:31,079
- He loves his university a lot. - Of course.

401
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,649
- He'll be a professor there. - Yes, you're giving a lecture.

402
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:35,080
- Really? - Yes.

403
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:36,319
Stop it.

404
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,680
- He's Professor Yoo now. - Right.

405
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,236
- There's a professor among us. - Hello.

406
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:40,360
Wait.

407
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,059
Again?

408
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:45,059
(Is he going to talk about his days at Sejong University again?)

409
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,099
I think that's the place.

410
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,699
- It must be the photo studio. - It's the photo studio.

411
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:50,030
- A photo studio. - It's in the Basement Level One.

412
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:52,330
- I see. Right here. - It's a photo studio.

413
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:53,570
It's this building.

414
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,669
- Let's go. - Let's go inside.

415
00:13:55,670 --> 00:13:56,770
This is...

416
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:59,950
Since I'm here, I should take photos for my resident registration card.

417
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:04,749
- They're waiting for us. - This must be it. "Soulmates."

418
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:07,820
- Right. They're soulmates. - Soulmates.

419
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:09,020
- Hello. - Hello.

420
00:14:09,021 --> 00:14:10,819
- You guys are the soulmates. - Hello.

421
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:11,890
Nice to meet you.

422
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,289
- Go ahead. - It's a photo studio here.

423
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:14,790
- Hello. - Hello.

424
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:17,089
- Where should I go? - Hello.

425
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,190
- Hello. - Go straight in.

426
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:20,359
You can go to the sofa.

427
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,330
- It's warm in here. - How spacious.

428
00:14:23,770 --> 00:14:25,630
- How spacious. - Hello.

429
00:14:26,170 --> 00:14:28,470
- I see clothes here too. - They have a lot of props.

430
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:31,669
- Check this place out. - How interesting.

431
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,150
(The inside of a trendy photo studio)

432
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:39,280
(It's cold. Close the door.)

433
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:40,896
(Thank you for coming. I'll sing a song for you.)

434
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,960
("I totally recommend this place." From Will Smith)

435
00:14:43,190 --> 00:14:44,490
This photo studio...

436
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,289
- It's quite unique. - Right.

437
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:47,720
What's the theme here?

438
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:50,860
It's different from a photo studio we were expecting.

439
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:53,700
We use CGI...

440
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,069
- for the photos. - Really?

441
00:14:56,070 --> 00:14:58,099
That's why they said they could fly in the sky.

442
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,199
("We can fly in the sky and turn into animals.")

443
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:02,909
I'm noticing that now. They do CGI editing on the photos.

444
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:04,039
(Photos with CGI effects are on the wall.)

445
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,110
- I see. - Right.

446
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:07,180
That's a fun theme.

447
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:08,510
You know what?

448
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,049
- They also add this kind of effect. - Right.

449
00:15:12,050 --> 00:15:13,220
His head is full of...

450
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,319
(This photo is right up his alley.)

451
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,650
His head is full of them.

452
00:15:18,090 --> 00:15:20,589
- In his brain... - I get the point.

453
00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:22,460
- But how should I put it? - Right.

454
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,760
- This one... - It's a bit lame.

455
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:26,900
- Did he actually take this photo? - Yes.

456
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,059
- This is an actual photo, right? - Yes.

457
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:29,100
This is...

458
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,670
Some people made letters with their body.

459
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,539
I see. L-O-V-E?

460
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:36,869
My gosh. So these photos have what we call...

461
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:38,540
- the quirky, low-budget feel. - Right.

462
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:41,510
(Imagination can turn into reality here.)

463
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,350
We don't force anything on our customers.

464
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,249
- But you added the CGI effect? - All of the photos...

465
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:46,680
Yes. That's what they wanted.

466
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,650
Do you make the CGI effects look obvious on purpose?

467
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,989
- That's our style. - That's what we do.

468
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:53,550
- That's also part of the theme? - Yes.

469
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,590
At first, we tried out the young adult theme.

470
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:59,089
We started with the American yearbook theme.

471
00:15:59,090 --> 00:16:01,200
- That was popular for a while. - That's right.

472
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,500
Actually, today is the graduation day.

473
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,200
Whose graduation is it?

474
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:09,099
I noticed it was the graduation day for Sejong University.

475
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:11,069
- Sejong University again? Come on. - My gosh.

476
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:12,509
- Hey! - That's enough.

477
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,009
- Stop it! - Seriously.

478
00:16:14,010 --> 00:16:16,079
- They... - It's too much. Let's go there!

479
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,479
- Let's go to Sejong University. - No. Listen.

480
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,620
- Let's talk about the photo studio. - Come on!

481
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,880
- I noticed it on our way here. - Come on!

482
00:16:22,050 --> 00:16:23,689
Kyung Nam, you also think he's taking too far, right?

483
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,520
- Gosh, this is way too much. - Right.

484
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:30,190
I guess Sejong University is the only thing on my mind.

485
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,500
Only Sejong University is on his mind.

486
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:37,600
What made you decide to open up a photo studio together?

487
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:42,170
We worked together on many projects before this.

488
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,080
We ran a vintage shop together.

489
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:46,840
- A vintage shop suits you well. - Right.

490
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:50,310
We ran a bar and a cafe together.

491
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,220
Then we started to use CGI on pictures.

492
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,550
We made our own T-shirts like this one.

493
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,820
- They're our dogs. - I see.

494
00:16:58,750 --> 00:16:59,789
You took a picture of them...

495
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:01,019
- and added the CGI effect. - Yes.

496
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,060
We started to make T-shirts for our friends.

497
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:06,530
- Then it turned into a business. - Yes.

498
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,399
Are you two friends?

499
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,469
Yes. We've been friends for eight years.

500
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:11,869
- You two went way back. - Yes.

501
00:17:11,870 --> 00:17:13,739
In your letter, you wrote that...

502
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,900
you were together for 16 hours a day.

503
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,810
Yes. We meet up in the morning.

504
00:17:18,210 --> 00:17:20,710
We go to the gym together in the morning.

505
00:17:20,810 --> 00:17:22,179
- You go to the gym together? - You go to the gym together?

506
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:24,010
- Yes. - Yes. We live in the same area.

507
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:25,479
We're neighbors.

508
